          "text": "Trunk-based development, where developers frequently merge their changes back to the mainline.",
          "isCorrect": true,
          "explanation": "Trunk-based development encourages developers to frequently merge their changes into the 'trunk' or mainline, usually at least once a day. This approach minimizes the likelihood of merge conflicts and ensures that code is integrated often, aligning well with Continuous Integration practices. The other branching strategies have their own merits but are not as aligned with the goals of minimizing merge conflicts and frequent code integration in a CI/CD context.",
