          "isCorrect": true,
          "explanation": "Taints and Tolerations in Kubernetes are used to repel a set of pods from a node based on certain criteria, such as hardware requirements or specific workloads. On the other hand, Node Affinity is used to attract pods to a set of nodes based on labels or other node attributes. This fundamental difference allows for precise control over pod placement in the cluster.",
